titleStmt.title: Óláfs saga hins helga (ed. Oscar Albert Johnsen, Kristiania 1922) : Upps DG 8 II : A digital edition

respStmt.resp: Digitisation of the text and its annotation in the slip archives of Gammelnorsk ordboksverk
respStmt.orgName: The Documentation Project (DokPro) University of Oslo

respStmt.resp: Regorganisation and revision of the encoded file

availability.p: Licence accepted by Christian-Emil Ore and Karl G. Johansson in mails to Odd Einar Haugen 29 October and 2 November 2015.

supportDesc.extent: 41 folios in 5 gatherings of 8 folios + 1 folio added at the end of gathering 5

foliation.p: In this edition, DG 8 II has been foliated separately from the other work contained in the same binding, DG 8 I (Magnus Lagabøtir’s landslǫg in the Frostuþing version).

origin.p: DG 8 II was written in Norway, c. 1225-1250.. Based on the dialect features, the codex was probably written in the Trondheim area.

projectDesc.p: This manuscript text has been encoded according to the standard set out in The Menota handbook (version 2.0 beta), at http://www.menota.org/guidelines as of 2008-07-24.

correction.p: This text is based on the text in the slip collection and the text in Ungers's edition and corrected against the manuscript

normalization.p: This text has been encoded on a diplomatic level

interpretation.p: The complete text except poetry has been lemmatised and morphologically analysed by the Gammelnorsk Ordboksverk and then transformed according to the rules specified in ch. 8 of the Menota Handbook, v. 2.0.

revisionDesc.change: 2020-09-12Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen: Revised the “history” element of the header

2020-02-24
Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen : (1) Changed all “mIM” name tokens (for imperative mood) with “mIP”; (2) Changed all “rPgM” name tokens with “rP gM” (adding a space between them)

2020-02-20
Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen : Made a single consistency correction of the me:msa name tokens

2016-03-29
Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen : (1) Changed the encoding of supplied hyphens from "supplied type="hyphenated"" to "pc type="supplied"" (for hyphens supplied by the editor, and lacking in the manuscript); (2) Made the file v. 1.0.6

2016-02-21
Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen : (1) Revised the "availability" element in the header with a CC-BY-SA 4.0 licence; (2) Made the file v. 1.2.3

2016-01-23
Odd Einar Haugen University of Bergen : (1) Replaced all 12 "me:punct type="supplied"" elements within "w" elements with "supplied type="hyphenated"" elements, so as to avoid having "me:punct" elements within "w" elements, which causes problems for the Corpuscle application; (2) Made the file v. 1.2.1
2011-01-13 Christian-Emil Ore, University of Oslo: (1) Generated new id numbers for all words.

2011-01-13 Odd Einar Haugen, University of Bergen: (1) Added xml:lang="lat" attribute to four identified Latin words (there may be more words in Latin), (2) changed encoding of numerals (identified by the "num" tag), so that all Roman numerals have Aarabic numbers as lemma form and "xUA" as grammatical form (me:msa attribute), (3) encoded "hvárt" as xAQ with "hvárt" as lemma form when it is used as a question particle, (4) made "annattveggia" and "annathvárt" in conjunction with "eða" into conjunctions (xCC) whether they are written in one or two words, similarly with "bæði" - "ok" (where both are analysed as conjunctions, xCC).

2011-01-12 Odd Einar Haugen, University of Bergen: (1) Disambiguated all 355 examples of alternative encoding using the delimiter "|", by introducing seven new categories, cAD = case is either accusative or dative, cAG = case is either accusative or genitive, mINSU = mood is either indicative or subjunctive, yINSU = the subjunction governs either indicative or subjunctive, yAD = the preposition governs either accusative or dative, yAG = the preposition governs either accusative or genitive, zAV = this word can also be analysed as an adverb, (2) identified all stanzas using "seg" elements with the type attribute "poetry", and numbered them from 1 to 63, (3) identified all numerals and put them into the element "num"; furthermore, made each into a separate word, e.g. "þrír tigir" was made into the two words "þrír" and "tigir", both contained in a single "num" element.

2011-01-05 Christian-Emil Ore, University of Oslo: (1) Replaced globally old word class tokens with new, e.g. "xCU" with "xCC" or "xCS", "xNU" with "xDQ" and "xNO" with "xAJ". (2) Generated new id numbers for all words.
2011-01-04 Odd Einar Haugen, University of Bergen: (1) Added missing text in four places, a total of 21 lines in the edition of O.A. Johnsen.

2010-12-30 Odd Einar Haugen, University of Bergen: (1) Added "div" elements for all 107 chapters, following O.A. Johnsen’s edition (1922). (2) Updated the physical description of the manuscript in the header.

2010-12-29 Odd Einar Haugen, University of Bergen: (1) Changed all character entities to Unicode characters, e.g. converting "eth" to "ð", so that the text should be more readable; the only exception being "jacute" for which there is no safe rendering. (2) Changed the element "expan" to "ex", according to TEI P5. (3) Interpreted slashes according to their usage, either signalling an entity (e.g. /av/ for the ligature "avlig"), a word divided over two lines, or a line continued on part of the following line (to avoid a short line at the end of a chapter). (4) Corrected "pb" and "lb" milestones a few places.

2007,2008
Christian-Emil Ore University of Oslo : Converted the electronic files (the transcription and the lemmatisation) into XML (Extensible Markup Language) according to the guidelines in the Menota handbook.
